  "prompt": "In this WordPress era, why do people still study coding instead of just using it?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why people continue to study coding despite the availability of platforms like WordPress:\n\n1. **Customization**: WordPress, while powerful and flexible, has its limitations. Learning to code allows individuals to create highly customized websites and applications tailored exactly to their needs, without being constrained by the limitations of pre-built themes and plugins.\n\n2. **Control and Flexibility**: Knowledge of coding gives developers full control over their projects. They can debug, optimize, and modify every aspect of their site without relying on external tools or third-party integrations.\n\n3. **Performance Optimization**: Coding skills enable developers to optimize the performance of their websites. Custom solutions can be more efficient and faster than generic plugins, leading to better user experience and SEO.\n\n4. **Security**: Understanding code means you can identify and mitigate security vulnerabilities more effectively. Relying solely on WordPress and third-party plugins can expose you to security risks.\n\n5. **Career Opportunities**: Coding is a valuable skill in the job market. Many tech careers require coding knowledge, and being able to build and maintain websites is a highly sought-after skill.\n\n6. **Learning and Growth**: Coding encourages logical thinking, problem-solving, and creativity. It\u2019s a continuous learning process that can be intellectually rewarding and fun.\n\n7. **Innovation and Experimentation**: Coders can innovate and experiment with new technologies, frameworks, and methodologies that provide unique opportunities not available through pre-built solutions.\n\n8. **Community Contribution**: Many coders enjoy contributing to open-source projects, including WordPress itself, which can be rewarding both personally and professionally.\n\n9. **Long-Term Savings**: Initially, using WordPress might seem cheaper, but custom solutions coded by oneself or an expert can save money in the long run as they might require fewer subscriptions, licenses, or paid plugins.\n\nIn conclusion, while WordPress is an excellent tool for building websites quickly and efficiently, there are significant advantages to learning coding skills that go beyond just the ability to use an existing platform.",
